profile_positions.description:
Member of 'Enhanced Technical Services Agreement’ (ETSA) team, seconded in Kuwait Oil Company (KOC). The role involves geological support for the North Kuwait Jurassic Group (NKJG) project, including hands-on 3D static modelling of tight carbonate reservoirs, technical advice on development & operations geology, and coaching KOC less experienced geologists. In addition, responsibilities cover geological support for Jurassic carbonates & unconventional reservoirs with HP & HT and high contents of sour H2S and acidic CO2 gases.   
PROJECT WORK:
•	Delivered 3D Static Matrix Models (Petrel tool/hands-on) for Upper & Lower Marrat formations (fractured & tight carbonate reservoirs). I separately modelled these reservoirs across 6 fields of the NKJG Project. When DFN models (natural fracture orientation, size & shape, etc.) were available, the scope of work included their upscaling to Matrix models. 
•	Built facies models; re-defined rock type, and then stochastically distributed new facies (SIS algorithm). Applied multiple distribution scenarios workflow for the Upper & Lower Marrat reservoirs to compare how modelling decisions and subsurface uncertainties influence the volume estimates.  
•	Estimated in-place STOIIP & GIIP volumes, analyses and reporting for multiple NKJG field reservoirs and blocks. Sensitivity analyses for P10, P50 and P90 volumetric realisations;
•	The sweet spots are mapped by applying various techniques, e.g., fractures & stress orientation, seismic curvature; 
 •	Delivered well-proposals (WP) for more than 20 wells drilled in fractured carbonates of Najmah Limestone and Middle Marrat formations; 
COORDINATION ROLE AND OTHER CONTRIBUTIONS TO RESERVOIR STUDIES:
•	Appraisal Planning and Conceptual Field Development Plan for Unconventional Najmah/Sargelu Formation, (April 2012); 
•	Bahrah Appraisal, Delineation, and Development (March 2013); 
•	The Appraisal Plan of the Upper and Lower Marrat Formations (Sept 2013); 
COACHING:
•	Coached KOC geologists

COORDINATOR for OPERATIONS GEOLOGY, WHILE DRILLING APPRAISAL KHAZAR-03 WELL:
•	Worked closely with the contract and procurement team on contract preparation & management for mudlogging and wellsite geology services (app. 1 mil US$). Coordinated activities with Well-Engineering and contractors while preparing staff mobilisations for drilling Khz-3 well (Caspian Sea);
•	Leading role in delivering Well Proposal (WP) for Khz-3 well. It was an integrated work with other subsurface disciplines  (e.g., PP, SI, RE) and Well Engineering team. Well is located on the east side of the Khazar Structure (behind the seismically interpreted faults). Contributed with geological inputs such as HC reservoir descriptions, prognoses of reservoir tops (L-B-H), pore-pressure & fluid-type predictions, indicate & analysed subsurface uncertainties (e.g., faults & trajectory intersections, heterogeneity, swelling clays, hard-strikes), geohazard (shallow gas) assessment & risk management, etc.;    
•	Managed wellsite geologist & mudlogging contractors (8+staff) on the 1 jack-up and maintained liaisons with service companies and KazNIPI (Kazakhstan Geological Institute);
•	I attended ‘Daily Operational’ and meetings with WSGs and reported to subsurface management on the daily progress of operations and the frequent problem-solving;
•	Attended ‘Operational Weekly’ and monthly KPI meetings with service companies; 
•	Post-DRILL: Delivered ‘quick-look’ analysis of wireline & MWD/LWD logs and provided preliminary probabilistic STOIIP volumes (used Shell's @RISK tool) after Khazar-3 drilled;
•	Synchronised stratigraphic analysis of Khazar Field with KazNIPI (Kazakhstan Geological Institute) and Shell's stratigraphic models to improve reserves-booking estimates and to complete Final Well Report;

•	Responsibilities for the full-field reservoir modelling of (e.g., deterministic, stochastic & scenarios) of ‘Khazar-Field’ located in the Caspian Sea/Kazakhstan. The project's scope included a conceptual model of 9 stacked reservoirs of deltaic environment, sedimentological field analysis, followed by structural, facies and property modelling (with one well on the structure); 
•	The model outputs were final stratigraphy & property cross-sections, various structural & properties maps, in-place STOIIP volumes, the model's back-calculated reservoir parameters, etc. The model was used as an input for dynamic modelling (MoReS), estimates of reserves, enhanced understanding of subsurface uncertainties prior to commencing the work on Field Development Planning (FDP) of the Khazar Field, and underpins the Well-Planning of Khazar-3 well; 
•	Delivered STOIIP Cumulative distribution curve (P10, P50, P90) / probabilistic volumes, Tornado Plots;
•	Delivered Fault Sealing and Fault Transmissibility Multipliers (FTM) studies;
•	Note: The Model was taken away to Aktau/Kazakhstan together with the team move in March 2010;

******OPERATIONS GEOLOGIST: Worked for client Dolphin Energy and partnered with Oxy & Total in Qatar (North Field / offshore). 
•	Provided geological support and frequent problems solving while batch-drilling 20 wells with two offshore drilling rigs (jack-up);
•	Participated in the well-planning of gas-condensate development wells (Khuff reservoir)
•	Responsibilities for planning site surveys and integration work with another discipline 
•	Reported operations progress & relevant issues to subsurface manager, weekly 
•	Attended operational meetings daily and monthly KPI meetings with service companies; 

******WELLSITE / OPERATIONS GEOLOGIST: Worked for client RasGas and partners ExxonMobil & Qatar Petroleum (QP); 
•	Wellsete Geologist (WSG) responsibilities on offshore jack-up were to supervise mudlogging and MWD/LWD contractors while drilling vertical & deviated development and occasionally appraisal wells through fractured carbonates of the North Field (high H2S contents);
•	Duties included, e.g., ‘quick-look analysis of e-logs, carbonate & clastic cuttings & core descriptions, HC evaluations (UV Box), casing, coring and well-TD picking depth, transfer data & reports, etc.
•	Reported to Ops Geologist  daily and attended operational meetings, etc

******WELL-SITE GEOLOGIST: Worked for clients BHP-Billiton in ALGERIA, onshore gas fields (Ohanet and Dimeta West Projects); drilling development (horizontal) wells through the Devonian clastic reservoirs. Duties include but are not limited to cuttings & core descriptions, HC evaluations (UV Box), casing, coring and well-TD picking depth, supervising mud-loggers, transferring data & reporting to the office daily. 

******WELL-SITE GEOLOGIST: Worked with clastic reservoirs for clients Fletcher Challenge Energy in NEW ZEALAND (onshore/offshore basins) of Pohokura, Tuihu, McKee, and Te Popo fields and for Phillips Petroleum in AUSTRALIA while drilling development wells in the Z.O.C.A. (Timor Sea);
